reviews.review_text: A typically good '84 show ! There are many show like this during this period, but I can't sneeze at this one !

Bobby's Whistle Bobby had a whistle around his neck that he was blowing during Sat Night.  After the song end, Phil grabbed the whistle and took off with it.  Bobby tried to get a "Phil, Give Me Back My Whistle" chant going and then said that he had a whole box of them at home as Day Job was starting.

This was a fun show and a great start of an incredible run

1st Official Taper Section This was the first Official Taper Section show....
What a Blessing this was & made getting mail order Taper tix a must for any serious taper. I remember walking into my first offical taper section thinking this is Heaven & about damn time....

Wang Dang Doodle This Wang Dang Doodle is embedded in my head. I can still remember it from about 20 years ago from tape I had and lost. I also remember the Women are Smarter. I also remember the psychedelics I took before listening to the tape...I still think this is the best Wang Dang Doodle I've heard. Great to hear it again. I've been looking for it...wasn't sure what show it was from. It's one of those things that never left me.

Butcher paper and pens in halls Took my HS GF to this one. I was 18 she 17, she was not a dead type girl and couldnt see my fascination with wanting to keep going to shows. She got it instantly when we walked in and sat in the second row until the person who had the tix for those seats came. We danced in the halls all eve, she loved it and was blown away. I recall this being a good night of many to come...

Everyone dosed Crazy show. Bill was passing out miracle tickets my friend was dropping everyone in line with a clean vile we had to share. The strange first Brent space was like a Joe Zawinal tribute with brother Mickey sticking it out with him.  (Thanks Mickey) B3 rolls on Black Peter chilling as usual. Always going to be one of my top shows.
Best of Grateful Dead I have been the biggest fan of grateful dead.
